All Classes

Class Description
AbstractPiece
A Reversi piece, which may be empty
Board
Holds Tiles, Sets Tile state during and after turns, Determines legal moves Tallies score
Color
Includes all possible states of a board tile in Reversi: A tile is either empty, contains a black piece, or contains a white piece.
ConsoleInterface
An input and output strategy using the console.
Controller
Controller class for coordinating Model and View to play a game of Reversi.
EmptyPiece
An empty Reversi Piece.
InputStrategy
Defines a strategy for collecting input from the turn player to make a move.
Message
Sends a message to the Controller.
MessageStream
A stream to send messages to display.
Model
The Model of a Reversi game.
NewGameMessage
Sends a message to start a new game to the Controller.
NewGameValve
Interprets a NewGameMessage, starting a new game of Reversi.
PlacePieceMessage
Sends a message to place a piece to the Controller.
PlacePieceValve
Interprets a PlacePieceMessage to place a new piece on the board.
Position
Immutable position (x, y) x is col, y is row
Reversi
Plays a game of Reversi
ReversiPiece
A Reversi piece that is not empty.
Tile
Models a Tile on a Reversi Board, Keeps track of its own state
TileIcon
An icon that contains a Reversi piece.
TileShell
The shell of a tile, including the ability to click to place a piece there.
UIStrategy
Defines a strategy for displaying output to the user.
Valve
Interprets a given Message.
ValveResponse
Responses that a valve may return MISS - Command not executed EXECUTED - Command executed ENDGAME - The game is over
View
The View for a Reversi game.
ViewTester
